Nigeria's security agents, at the behest of President Muhammadu, are threatening to bring down as they seek to arrest staffers of the online news platform. "Open the gate! Come outside," the menacing security agents said. They are currently banging on the gate repeatedly. "What are you doing here? "Is this Sahara Reporters office?" the agents yelled at security guards of the online news platform. The banging and yelling continue.



